data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[əb'tju:s]
*tính từ
 ■cùn, nhụt
 ⁃an obtuse knife
 dao cùn
 ■(toán học) tù
 ⁃an obtuse angle
 góc tù
 ■chậm hiểu, trì độn
 ■âm ỉ
 ⁃an obtuse pain
 đau âm ỉ

Anh - Anh
obtuse
■ adjective
1》 annoyingly insensitive or slow to understand.
2》 (of an angle) more than 90° and less than 180°.
3》 not sharp-pointed or sharp-edged; blunt.
Derivatives
obtuselyadverb
obtusenessnoun
obtusitynoun
Origin
ME: from L. obtusus, obtundere, from ob- 'against' + tundere 'to beat'.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
obtuse
▸ adjective STUPID, foolish, slow-witted, slow, dull-witted, unintelligent, ignorant, simple-minded; insensitive, imperceptive, uncomprehending; informal dim, dim-witted, dense, dumb, slow on the uptake, half-witted, brain-dead, moronic, cretinous, thick, dopey, dozy, wooden-headed, boneheaded; Brit.informal divvy; Scottish & N. Englishinformal glaikit; N. Amer.informal chowderheaded.
Opposites
clever.
